---
const steps = [
  {
    icon: '\u{1F3AF}',
    title: 'Set your priorities',
    description: "Giving, saving, bills. These come off the top, not from leftovers.",
  },
  {
    icon: '\u{1F4C4}',
    title: 'Import your transactions',
    description: "One file from your bank, once a week. Two minutes. Your data stays in your hands.",
  },
  {
    icon: '\u2705',
    title: 'See your number',
    description: "Safe-to-Spend updates. Green means go. Spend freely within it.",
  },
];
---

<section id="how-it-works" class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white scroll-mt-16">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900">
        Simple by design.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 lg:gap-12">
      {steps.map((step, index) => (
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-16 h-16 rounded-2xl bg-storehouse-100 text-3xl mb-6">
            {step.icon}
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-2 mb-3">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-storehouse-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold flex items-center justify-center">
              {index + 1}
            </span>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">
              {step.title}
            </h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            {step.description}
          </p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto p-6 bg-storehouse-50 rounded-xl border border-storehouse-200">
      <p class="text-center text-lg text-slate-700 font-medium">
        Storehouse auto-categorizes your spending so you can see where your money went &mdash; but it never limits where it can go.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-center text-slate-600">
        One number determines what you can spend. Categories are the rearview mirror, not the steering wheel.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
